  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO AMEND SECTION 57-73-23, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972, TO MODIFY THE CONDITIONS UNDER WHICH CERTAIN EMPLOYERS PROVIDING CHILD CARE STIPENDS MAY BE ELIGIBLE FOR AN INCOME TAX CREDIT UNDER THE SECTION; TO PROVIDE THAT THE CREDIT ALLOWED MAY NOT EXCEED $3,000.00 PER YEAR FOR EACH CHILD OF A PARTICIPATING EMPLOYEE; TO REVISE CERTIFICATION REQUIREMENTS EMPLOYERS MUST MEET; TO PROVIDE AN ANNUAL AGGREGATE CAP OF $1,000,000.00 ON CREDITS THAT MAY BE ALLOCATED UNDER THIS SECTION; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
  },
